text: Saad Ashraf (born 25 September 1997) is an English cricketer. In 2017, he was named the Young Player of the Year in the Nottinghamshire Premier League. He made his first-class debut on 26 March 2019, for Leeds/Bradford MCCU against Derbyshire, as part of the Marylebone Cricket Club University fixtures. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:English cricketers Category:Leeds/Bradford MCCU cricketers Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
